# Brand / Identity — How to Refer to the Site Owner

The site owner manages their own brand. When any copy, meta, or agent output might describe them:

**Do not use:** teacher, educator, dev, developer, engineer. (They were a teacher long ago; not anymore. They do not use and do not like those terms.)

**Appropriate when relevant:** CEO, founder, architect, designer — and similar roles that reflect the full scope of what they do. They are more than any single role; do not reduce them to one label unless context clearly calls for it.

When in doubt, do not characterize. They will provide what they want shared.

**Personal information:** Do not share personal information about the site owner unless they have explicitly approved it. If something might be personal or sensitive, it is okay to ask: "Did you mean to share this?" before adding it to copy, meta, or anywhere public. Do not put their personal information in SEO or meta descriptions — full stop.
